</div><div class="ad-wrapper recipe-details-ad"><span class="ad-label">ADVERTISEMENT</span><div class="ad-slot recipe-description-ad-wrapper adunitContainer"><div class="adBox" id="recipe-details-ad"></div></div></div><div class="recipe-ingredients"><h2 class="recipe-ingredients-title">ingredients</h2><div class="subrecipe"><div class="subrecipe-ingredients"><div class="subrecipe-ingredients--quantity">½</div><div class="subrecipe-ingredients--name">lb instant ramen (from 2 packs regular size or 3 packs small size), discarding soup packets – note 1</div><div class="subrecipe-ingredients--quantity">100g</div><div class="subrecipe-ingredients--name">pancetta or guanciale or 2 slices thick-cut bacon, cut into ¼” strips or cubes</div><div class="subrecipe-ingredients--quantity">1</div><div class="subrecipe-ingredients--name">whole egg</div><div class="subrecipe-ingredients--quantity">3</div><div class="subrecipe-ingredients--name">egg yolks</div><div class="subrecipe-ingredients--quantity">1</div><div class="subrecipe-ingredients--name">cup (75g) grated Pecorino Romano and/or Parmigiana Reggiano, plus more for finishing (tip: grate on small hole side of box grater, not microplane which is too fine)</div><div class="subrecipe-ingredients--quantity"></div><div class="subrecipe-ingredients--name">Fresh ground black pepper</div><div class="subrecipe-ingredients--quantity"></div><div class="subrecipe-ingredients--name">Reserved ramen cooking water</div></div></div><div class="ingredient-substitution-link"><a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="/ingredient-substitutions/">Ingredient Substitution Guide</a></div></div><div class="ad-wrapper recipe-ingredients-ad"><span class="ad-label">ADVERTISEMENT</span><div class="ad-slot recipe-ingredients-ad-wrapper adunitContainer"><div class="adBox" id="recipe-ingredients-ad"></div></div></div><div class="recipe-directions"><h2 class="recipe-directions-title">directions</h2><div class="recipe-notes"><div class="recipe-notes-title">Notes</div><p class="recipe-notes-text">Use 2 packs of regular-sized ramen (115g brick) or 3 packs of small-sized ramen (75g brick). Use traditional deep-fried or air-fried instant ramen.</p></div><div class="recipe-directions-image"><div class="corus-image-wrapper" style="max-width:1280px;margin:auto"><img alt="" loading="lazy" width="1280" height="853" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" class="recipe-directions-image-file" style="color:transparent;width:100%;height:auto" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcSet="https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-prep.jpg?w=640&amp;quality=75 640w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-prep.jpg?w=704&amp;quality=75 704w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-prep.jpg?w=750&amp;quality=75 750w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-prep.jpg?w=828&amp;quality=75 828w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-prep.jpg?w=856&amp;quality=75 856w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-prep.jpg?w=1080&amp;quality=75 1080w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-prep.jpg?w=1200&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-prep.jpg?w=1920&amp;quality=75 1920w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-prep.jpg?w=2048&amp;quality=75 2048w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-prep.jpg?w=3840&amp;quality=75 3840w" src="https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-prep.jpg?w=3840&amp;quality=75"/></div></div><div class="recipe-step"><div id="step1" class="recipe-step-title">Step 1</div><div class="recipe-step-content"><p>Bring a medium pot of (unsalted) water to a boil. We want this ready to quickly cook the ramen.</p></div></div><div class="recipe-step"><div id="step2" class="recipe-step-title">Step 2</div><div class="recipe-step-content"><p>Set a heavy-bottom pan on the stove and place pancetta (or guanciale or bacon) pieces into the cold pan without any oil. Turn heat to medium to medium-high and allow the meat to slowly render its fat and start to crisp and brown on the edges, stirring occasionally. Scoop out and set aside, leaving rendered fat in the pot. Leave pot on the burner on lowest heat to keep warm.</p></div><div class="recipe-step-image"><div class="corus-image-wrapper" style="max-width:1280px;margin:auto"><img alt="Pancetta cooking on a stovetop" loading="lazy" width="1280" height="853" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" class="recipe-step-image-file" style="color:transparent;width:100%;height:auto" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcSet="https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Pancetta-cooking.jpg?w=640&amp;quality=75 640w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Pancetta-cooking.jpg?w=704&amp;quality=75 704w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Pancetta-cooking.jpg?w=750&amp;quality=75 750w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Pancetta-cooking.jpg?w=828&amp;quality=75 828w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Pancetta-cooking.jpg?w=856&amp;quality=75 856w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Pancetta-cooking.jpg?w=1080&amp;quality=75 1080w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Pancetta-cooking.jpg?w=1200&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Pancetta-cooking.jpg?w=1920&amp;quality=75 1920w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Pancetta-cooking.jpg?w=2048&amp;quality=75 2048w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Pancetta-cooking.jpg?w=3840&amp;quality=75 3840w" src="https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Pancetta-cooking.jpg?w=3840&amp;quality=75"/></div></div></div><div class="recipe-step"><div id="step3" class="recipe-step-title">Step 3</div><div class="recipe-step-content"><p>While meat is rendering in step 2, place whole egg, egg yolks, grated cheese and a generous amount of freshly ground black pepper into a mixing bowl and whisk well. Set aside.</p></div><div class="recipe-step-image"><div class="corus-image-wrapper" style="max-width:1280px;margin:auto"><img alt="Carbonara Ramen ingredients in a mixing bowl" loading="lazy" width="1280" height="853" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" class="recipe-step-image-file" style="color:transparent;width:100%;height:auto" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcSet="https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-ingredients-in-a-mixing-bowl.jpg?w=640&amp;quality=75 640w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-ingredients-in-a-mixing-bowl.jpg?w=704&amp;quality=75 704w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-ingredients-in-a-mixing-bowl.jpg?w=750&amp;quality=75 750w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-ingredients-in-a-mixing-bowl.jpg?w=828&amp;quality=75 828w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-ingredients-in-a-mixing-bowl.jpg?w=856&amp;quality=75 856w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-ingredients-in-a-mixing-bowl.jpg?w=1080&amp;quality=75 1080w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-ingredients-in-a-mixing-bowl.jpg?w=1200&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-ingredients-in-a-mixing-bowl.jpg?w=1920&amp;quality=75 1920w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-ingredients-in-a-mixing-bowl.jpg?w=2048&amp;quality=75 2048w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-ingredients-in-a-mixing-bowl.jpg?w=3840&amp;quality=75 3840w" src="https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-ingredients-in-a-mixing-bowl.jpg?w=3840&amp;quality=75"/></div></div></div><div class="recipe-step"><div id="step4" class="recipe-step-title">Step 4</div><div class="recipe-step-content"><p>As soon as pancetta is scooped out, plunge ramen noodles into pot of boiling water. Use tongs or chopsticks to encourage untangling as soon as softened enough to do so. Cook ramen briefly, until strands are fully cooked through but still on the firmer side (I find this typically takes less time than package directions). Taste test a strand to make sure. Instant ramen can go from perfectly cooked to soggy pretty quickly.</p></div></div><div class="recipe-step"><div id="step5" class="recipe-step-title">Step 5</div><div class="recipe-step-content"><p>One tablespoon at a time, scoop 4 tablespoons (for a total equivalent of ¼ cup) of noodle cooking water into the egg mixture, whisking after each addition to temper the mixture — i.e. slowly bring up the temperature such that it doesn’t scramble in the next step.</p></div></div><div class="recipe-step"><div id="step6" class="recipe-step-title">Step 6</div><div class="recipe-step-content"><p>Use tongs to transfer noodles directly from boiling water into the pot of rendered fat. We don’t mind some of the cooking water clinging to the noodles. Pour egg mixture over top. Use tongs to toss and move the noodles and sauce around vigorously to emulsify the fat and melt the cheese.</p></div><div class="recipe-step-image"><div class="corus-image-wrapper" style="max-width:1280px;margin:auto"><img alt="" loading="lazy" width="1280" height="853" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" class="recipe-step-image-file" style="color:transparent;width:100%;height:auto" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcSet="https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-mixing-in-a-pot.jpg?w=640&amp;quality=75 640w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-mixing-in-a-pot.jpg?w=704&amp;quality=75 704w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-mixing-in-a-pot.jpg?w=750&amp;quality=75 750w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-mixing-in-a-pot.jpg?w=828&amp;quality=75 828w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-mixing-in-a-pot.jpg?w=856&amp;quality=75 856w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-mixing-in-a-pot.jpg?w=1080&amp;quality=75 1080w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-mixing-in-a-pot.jpg?w=1200&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-mixing-in-a-pot.jpg?w=1920&amp;quality=75 1920w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-mixing-in-a-pot.jpg?w=2048&amp;quality=75 2048w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-mixing-in-a-pot.jpg?w=3840&amp;quality=75 3840w" src="https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Carbonara-Ramen-mixing-in-a-pot.jpg?w=3840&amp;quality=75"/></div></div></div></div><ul class="post-tags"><li class="post-tag"><a class="button-primary post-tag-link" href="/tag/30-minutes-or-less/">30 minutes or less</a></li><li class="post-tag"><a class="button-primary post-tag-link" href="/tag/comfort-food/">comfort food</a></li><li class="post-tag"><a class="button-primary post-tag-link" href="/tag/cooking-with-kids/">cooking with kids</a></li><li class="post-tag"><a class="button-primary post-tag-link" href="/tag/dinner/">dinner</a></li><li class="post-tag"><a class="button-primary post-tag-link" href="/tag/lunch/">lunch</a></li></ul><div id="rate-recipe-anchor" class="bottom-recipe-rating-container"><h2 class="section-title">Rate Recipe</h2><div id="bottom-recipe-rating-section" class="recipe-ratings"><div class="recipe-title"><s